titleInfo.title: United States of America v. $35,000.00 in United States Currency
titleInfo.subTitle: SCHEDULING ORDER. Claimant shall file a brief in support of his Motion to Suppress Evidence and Statements 28 no later than 5/29/2009. The United States is given until 6/19/2009 to respond to the claimant's brief. The claimant may file a reply brief within the time allowed by NECivR 7.0.1(c). The Motion 28 will be set for an evidentiary hearing, to be held after the briefing schedule expires. The trial now set for 5/27/2009 is cancelled and will be rescheduled after the court rules on the claimant's Motion to Suppress. Ordered by Magistrate Judge F. A. Gossett. (CLS, )
